MOSCOW, Dec. 8 (Xinhua) -- Russia confirmed 30,752 new coronavirus cases in the past 24 hours, taking the nationwide tally to 9,895,597, said the official monitoring and response center on Wednesday. The nationwide death toll increased 1,179 to 284,823, while the number of recoveries increased 36,976 to 8,602,067. Meanwhile, Moscow, Russia's worst-hit region, reported 3,004 new cases, taking its total to 1,971,951. Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin said Tuesday that the country must "prepare for any turn of events" amid the spread of the Omicron strain. He added that it remained unclear how the new strain would affect the spread of the virus, and the government was finalizing a comprehensive plan of action to tackle the infection. Mishustin called the country's situation "tense," saying that coronavirus cases were on the rise in Russia's 11 regions last week. According to official data, about 64 million Russians had been fully vaccinated as of Friday, while 72 million had received at least one dose of the vaccine. Enditem